11:01 AM Defendant Frank L. DiDomenico in court, in custody.  Attorney Annie E Getsinger in court for Frank L. DiDomenico.  Prosecuting attorney Rick C Spoentgen in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states cases and appearances.  Atty Getsinger acknowledges rec. complaint in 22CF585 and waives reading noting DE hasn't applied for PD yet in 22CF585 but it's likely he will qualify.  Court advises DE re: applying.  Court advises DE of charges/max penalties in 22CF585.  State makes statement re: bond on 22CF585 - requests $750 cash.  Atty Getsinger responds - requests signature bond.  Court orders $150 cash bond.  Parties discuss scheduling as to all 3 criminal cases.  Atty Getsinger believes the cases may be resolved but will defer to the Court noting they are ready to proceed to waiver of prelim in 22CF303 today.  Court notes motion to amend information.  Atty Getsinger requests all 3 cases be reset to the Court's next intake noting she thinks they'll be stipulated.  Court notes if DE waives time limits in 22CF585 she could schedule all matters for PH/WOPH/ARGN at the same time.  Atty Getsinger responds - she's unsure how all the cases will go at this time.  State responds/requests motion be granted to amend as there is no basis for DE to object.  Court responds.  Atty Getsinger responds/agrees w/statement by the State.  Atty Getsinger would agree w/motion to amend in 22CF5 - Court grants that motion.  Court grants request to reset all matters together one more time but after that they will all be set for trial.
